    { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can I use ContextKit CLI in CI pipelines?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes. The CLI returns exit code 0 for scores of 5 or higher and exit code 1 for lower scores. Add npx contextkit score to your GitHub Actions workflow to enforce config quality on every pull request." }},
    { "@type": "Question", "name": "What config files does ContextKit CLI support?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "ContextKit auto-detects CLAUDE.md, .claude/CLAUDE.md, .cursorrules, .cursor/rules, AGENTS.md, codex.md, and GEMINI.md. You can also pass any file path directly: npx contextkit score path/to/config.md." }},
